\name{multiomfigR-package}
\alias{multiomfigR-package}
\alias{multiomfigR}
\title{NC-Style Multi-Omics Integration Figure Toolkit}
\description{
Local R toolkit for NC-style multi-omics integration figures from source-data tables.
}
\details{
The package is source-data-first and supports integrated embeddings, modality
metrics, cross-dataset validation heatmaps, regulatory or feature-link networks,
pathway/program heatmaps, and composite multi-omics figures. It depends on
\pkg{ncfigR} for shared theme, layout, and export.
}
